Coleophora polycarpaeae is a moth of the family Coleophoridae. It is found on the Canary Islands.
The larvae feed on Polycarpaea divaricata and Polycarpaea smithii. They create an off-white to greyish brown tubular leaf case of 4.5â€“5 mm long. Dorsally it is often covered with fragments of frass or detritus.